```

---

## Bottom line

This file has **no exploitable injection, auth-bypass, or crypto flaws today** because it does almost nothing with user input. The real risk is **defense-in-depth gaps** (headers, rate limiting, logging, auth scaffolding) that will become serious the moment `/users` is backed by a database or accepts query parameters. Address the hardening items above before adding any feature that touches user input or real data.

